title: LEGCO QUESTION NO.1 (Oral Reply)
question_text: Question : The authorities revealed to this Council in January this year that they hoped to establish a system for collecting from various organisations comprehensive information on cases of suicide. In this connection, will the Government inform this Council of : (a) the progress with regard to the system; whether it has used the information collected by the system to analyse the relationship of suicidal behaviour to the economic downturn and unemployment; if so, of the findings; (b) the services currently provided to the unemployed to prevent them from committing suicide; whether it

Kong Council of Social Service operates a "District-based Network Employment Support

addition to the Government’s on-going efforts to create more job opportunities, to

and family caseworkers in Family Service Centres always provide ready assistance to
families of individuals who have committed or attempted suicide. They provide counselling
services to the families to help them come to terms with the situation. Practical
assistance in the form of financial assistance is provided to needy families, and
referrals for residential care or other community support services such as home help
services are made, as appropriate. Clinical psychological service or psychiatric treatment
is available for those who require more intensive intervention assistance. Family caseworkers work

with their clients and their family members to evaluate the progress and success of the agreed treatment plan. The effectiveness of the services provided is also assessed on the basis of the ability of the affected individual to resume their normal pattern of life.

interdepartmental Working Group comprising representatives from the Health and Welfare
Bureau, Social Welfare Department, Hospital Authority and the Department of Health was set
up to examine how statistics on suicide cases should be collected and the information
analyzed. A new data collection system was introduced in April of this year. The Hospital
Authority records the number of patient discharges and deaths in its hospitals resulting
from suicide. The Social Welfare Department collects information on cases handled by
social workers in all Family Service Centres and its medical social work units.
